Decorator has-a component (composition), not is-a subclass (inheritance).

8ï¸âƒ£ Simple Real-Life Analogy (Non-Food)
ğŸ® Video Game Character

Base character â†’ can run

Add armor â†’ extra protection

Add weapon â†’ extra attack

Add shield â†’ extra defense

ğŸ‘‰ You wrap character with abilities
ğŸ‘‰ Same character, different powers
ğŸ‘‰ Added dynamically

This is Decorator Pattern.

9ï¸âƒ£ Simple Python Example
# Component
class Notifier:
    def send(self, message):
        pass


# Concrete Component
class EmailNotifier(Notifier):
    def send(self, message):
        return f"Email sent: {message}"


# Decorator
class NotifierDecorator(Notifier):
    def __init__(self, notifier):
        self.notifier = notifier


# Concrete Decorators
class SMSDecorator(NotifierDecorator):
    def send(self, message):
        return self.notifier.send(message) + " | SMS sent"


class WhatsAppDecorator(NotifierDecorator):
    def send(self, message):
        return self.notifier.send(message) + " | WhatsApp sent"

Usage
notifier = EmailNotifier()
notifier = SMSDecorator(notifier)
notifier = WhatsAppDecorator(notifier)

print(notifier.send("Hello"))

Output
Email sent: Hello | SMS sent | WhatsApp sent

ğŸ” What Happened Here?

Email â†’ base behavior

SMS â†’ added without modifying Email class

WhatsApp â†’ added dynamically

Same object, extended behavior

10ï¸âƒ£ Decorator vs Inheritance
Decorator	Inheritance
Runtime behavior	Compile-time behavior
Flexible	Rigid
Avoids class explosion	Causes class explosion
Uses composition	Uses inheritance
11ï¸âƒ£ Decorator vs Adapter (Very Important)
Decorator	Adapter
Adds new behavior	Converts interface
Same interface	Different interface
Enhances object	Makes incompatible classes work
12ï¸âƒ£ SOLID Principles Followed

âœ… Open-Closed Principle

âœ… Single Responsibility Principle

âœ… Composition over Inheritance

13ï¸âƒ£ Advantages

Flexible and extensible

No modification of existing code

Dynamic behavior addition

Cleaner than inheritance

14ï¸âƒ£ Disadvantages

Many small classes

Harder debugging if overused

Order of decorators may matter

15ï¸âƒ£ Interview One-Liners

