17ï¸âƒ£ Very Short Exam Answer (4â€“5 lines)

Decorator Pattern is a structural design pattern used to add new responsibilities to an object dynamically. It avoids subclass explosion and follows the Open-Closed Principle. It uses composition instead of inheritance. Decorators wrap objects and enhance their behavior at runtime.